2. NewsArenaIndia (Politics)¶

In [ ]: 
# Configure
  c = twint.Config()
  c.Username = "NewsArenaIndia"
  c.Limit = 1000
  c.Pandas = True
  # Run
  twint.run.Search(c)

  #Store it in DataFrame
  Tweets_df = twint.storage.panda.Tweets_df

  #Create Functions to get column names and extract required column dataframe
  def column_names():
      return twint.output.panda.Tweets_df.columns
  def twint_to_pd(columns):
      return twint.output.panda.Tweets_df[columns]

  tweet_df = twint_to_pd(["tweet"])
  x = ["Politics"]*len(tweet_df.axes[0])
  x = pd.DataFrame(x,columns =["class"])
  tweet_df["class"] = x

  tweet_df.to_csv("data.csv", mode ='a', encoding = 'utf-8-sig')

# Configure
  c = twint.Config()
  c.Username = "indianscinews"
  c.Limit = 1000
  c.Pandas = True
  # Run
  twint.run.Search(c)

  #Store it in DataFrame
  Tweets_df = twint.storage.panda.Tweets_df

  #Create Functions to get column names and extract required column dataframe
  def column_names():
      return twint.output.panda.Tweets_df.columns
  def twint_to_pd(columns):
      return twint.output.panda.Tweets_df[columns]

  tweet_df = twint_to_pd(["tweet"])
  x = ["SpaceNews"]*len(tweet_df.axes[0])
  x = pd.DataFrame(x,columns =["class"])
  tweet_df["class"] = x

  tweet_df.to_csv("data.csv", mode ='a', encoding = 'utf-8-sig')

Removing the unwanted text from tweets¶

In [ ]: 
#preprocessing

  import re
  import string

  def urlRemove(tweet):
      tweet=re.sub(r"(?i)\b((?:https?://|www\d{0,3}[.]|[a-z0-9.\-]+[.][a-z]{2,4}/)(?:[^\s()<>]+|\(([^\s()<>]+|(\([^\s()<>]+\)))*\))+(?:\(([^\s()<>]+|(\([^\s()<>]+\)))*\)|[^\s`!()\[\]{};:'\".,<>?«»“”‘’]))",'',tweet)
      tweet=tweet.strip().replace('\n', '')
      tweet="".join([i for i in tweet if i not in string.punctuation])
      tweet=re.sub(r'\s+', ' ', tweet)
      return tweet.lower()

Applying stop word filtering, tokenization and lemmatization¶

In [ ]: 
import nltk
  from nltk.stem import WordNetLemmatizer

  def lemmatizeTweet(tweet):
      tokens=re.split(' ',tweet)
      stopwords=nltk.corpus.stopwords.words('english')
      tokens= [i for i in tokens if i not in stopwords]
      lemmatizer=WordNetLemmatizer()
      lemm_text = [lemmatizer.lemmatize(word) for word in tokens]
      lemm_text=" ".join(lemm_text)
      return lemm_text

In [ ]: 
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split

  x_train,x_test,y_train,y_test=train_test_split(x,y,test_size=0.2)

  #vectorization
  from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer

  tf_idf=TfidfVectorizer(ngram_range=(1,2))

  x_train=tf_idf.fit_transform(x_train)
  x_test=tf_idf.transform(x_test)

  #converting sparse matrix to array
  x_train=x_train.toarray()
  x_test=x_test.toarray()
